Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
to cross the street, you should find a cross first. if there is a traffic light, push the button to cross the street. when the traffic light shows that you can cross the street, you can go ahead and cross the street. if there isn't a traffic light, you should look around and see if there are cars coming. you can cross the street when no car is coming. always keep an eye on the traffic.